The Hellenic Police or FRONTEX may decide to detain you in the Detention Center of the First Reception and Identification Center (Moria) in exceptional cases (if they see no other way) for the following reasons: 

a. to verify your true identity or country of origin;

 b. when they have reasons to believe that there is a high risk of escape;

 c. when they have reasons to believe that you are applying for international protection only to delay or frustrate the enforcement of a return decision; or 

 d. if your presence in Greece is considered a threat to national security or public order.
